  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> good guys basic idea:<br>
start gandalf and use his gimmicks to win.  the allies are solid, the events are busted and glamdring is fun.  <br>
the fellowship is all about going slow to site 3, then setting up a good fellowship hand and running from site 3-6 (if you get aragorn out).<br>
don&#39;t bid high.  your sites help you catch up for the most part.  site 3 can help you comeback from a bad start.  use versatility and aimed archery to kill most minions.  sting/glamdring help reduce the pool.  use gandalf to fight cause he can get big when you pump him with his events.<br>
you can always get to site 3 first turn.  stop and heal.  get more fellowship cards in hand, then run to site 6. then go 7-8, then to 9.  your sites are sometimes helpful to your fellowship and sometimes to your minions.  dont exhaust anyone unless you have to due to cards like hate going around.  there are plenty of allies.  use them as much as you can and suicide them at thier home if possible.  use strength of spirit with legolas or aragorns bow, its solid. lmk questions.<br>
<br>
the shadow is just to cycle your had for fellowship cards.  however if your opponent gets greedy a swarm can overwhelm frodo if they arent careful. <br>
try for a big troll at 4 or 5 or both to slow the opponent.  the hammer isnt needed but is good if they dont have armor.  this deck has more conditionbs than most moria decks, but it is ok cause you have extras if some get discarded with cards like albert dreary and stuff.  dont worry about versatility it does nothing to 1 vitality guys anyway.  your minions will never do well vs archery except mabey in moria or if its the troll, but thats ok cause they aren&#39;t the main focus. you usually win bu going to 9 first.<br>
<br>
lmk what you think<br>
